mibusmUserProfileTable.name: mibusmUserProfileTable
mibusmUserProfileTable.description: A list of mibusmUserProfile profile entries.

mibusmUserProfileEntry.name: mibusmUserProfileEntry
mibusmUserProfileEntry.description: A mibusmUserProfile entry containing objects that maps to the parameters of mibusmUserProfile profile.

usmUserProfile_Name.name: usmUserProfile_Name
usmUserProfile_Name.description: The user (principal) on whose behalf the message is being exchange.

usmUserProfile_ActiveEnabled.name: usmUserProfile_ActiveEnabled
usmUserProfile_ActiveEnabled.description: TRUE if this user is enabled for message exchange.

usmUserProfile_ReadWriteAccess.name: usmUserProfile_ReadWriteAccess
usmUserProfile_ReadWriteAccess.description: TRUE if this user is configured for read-write access to MIB view.

usmUserProfile_AuthProtocol.name: usmUserProfile_AuthProtocol
usmUserProfile_AuthProtocol.description: Indicate whether messages sent on behalf of this user to/from the SNMP engine can be authenticated and,if so, the type of authentication protocol to be used.

usmUserProfile_PrivProtocol.name: usmUserProfile_PrivProtocol
usmUserProfile_PrivProtocol.description: Indicate whether messages sent on behalf of this user to/from the SNMP engine can be protected by encryption and,if so, the type of privacy protocol to be used.

usmUserProfile_AuthKey.name: usmUserProfile_AuthKey
usmUserProfile_AuthKey.description: The user's authkey: calculated based on password and auth protocol. This can be set using snmpAuthPass command

usmUserProfile_PrivKey.name: usmUserProfile_PrivKey
usmUserProfile_PrivKey.description: The user's privacy: key calculated based on priv-password and auth protocol. This can be set using snmpPrivPass command

mibsnmpManagerProfileTable.name: mibsnmpManagerProfileTable
mibsnmpManagerProfileTable.description: A list of mibsnmpManagerProfile profile entries.

mibsnmpManagerProfileEntry.name: mibsnmpManagerProfileEntry
mibsnmpManagerProfileEntry.description: A mibsnmpManagerProfile entry containing objects that maps to the parameters of mibsnmpManagerProfile profile.

snmpManagerProfile_Name.name: snmpManagerProfile_Name
snmpManagerProfile_Name.description: The name or the ip-address in dot format of the SNMP Manager (host) to send SNMP requests to the TAOS SNMP Agent. When DNS or YP/NIS is supported this name will be used to look up the LAN address.

snmpManagerProfile_Active.name: snmpManagerProfile_Active
snmpManagerProfile_Active.description: TRUE if SNMP messages from a particular SNMP Manager should be processed. This implies read-access for SNMPv1.

snmpManagerProfile_WriteAccess.name: snmpManagerProfile_WriteAccess
snmpManagerProfile_WriteAccess.description: When set to `no' (its default value), the SNMP agent only allows read requests. When set to 'yes', the SNMP agent allows write requests in addition to read requests.

snmpManagerProfile_SnmpMessageType.name: snmpManagerProfile_SnmpMessageType
snmpManagerProfile_SnmpMessageType.description: Indicate the message type that the SNMP agent should allow for this SNMP Manager.

mibsnmpProfileTable.name: mibsnmpProfileTable
mibsnmpProfileTable.description: A list of mibsnmpProfile profile entries.

mibsnmpProfileEntry.name: mibsnmpProfileEntry
mibsnmpProfileEntry.description: A mibsnmpProfile entry containing objects that maps to the parameters of mibsnmpProfile profile.

snmpProfile_Enabled.name: snmpProfile_Enabled
snmpProfile_Enabled.description: When set to `no' (its default value), the unit cannot be accessed via SNMP.

snmpProfile_ReadCommunity.name: snmpProfile_ReadCommunity
snmpProfile_ReadCommunity.description: The SNMP community name for read access.

snmpProfile_ReadWriteEnabled.name: snmpProfile_ReadWriteEnabled
snmpProfile_ReadWriteEnabled.description: When set to `no' (its default value), the write community cannot be accessed via SNMP.

snmpProfile_ReadWriteCommunity.name: snmpProfile_ReadWriteCommunity
snmpProfile_ReadWriteCommunity.description: The SNMP community name for read/write access.

snmpProfile_EnforceAddressSecurity.name: snmpProfile_EnforceAddressSecurity
snmpProfile_EnforceAddressSecurity.description: When set to `no' (its default value), we will allow access to all SNMP managers that know the community string. When set to `yes', we will check the source IP address against the ones that are defined in the SNMP-MANAGER profiles before allowing access.

snmpProfile_EarlyQueueDiscard.name: snmpProfile_EarlyQueueDiscard
snmpProfile_EarlyQueueDiscard.description: If this parameter is set to yes, the system will filter and discard the requests from unauthorized host before queuing to the SNMP UDP port 161. If this parameter is set to no, the system will queue all incoming SNMP requests to SNMP layer which will discard the requests later if they are from unauthorized host.

snmpProfile_Contact.name: snmpProfile_Contact
snmpProfile_Contact.description: The name of the contact for this device. SNMP readable and settable.

snmpProfile_Location.name: snmpProfile_Location
snmpProfile_Location.description: The location of this device. SNMP readable and settable.

snmpProfile_QueueDepth.name: snmpProfile_QueueDepth
snmpProfile_QueueDepth.description: The maximum number of SNMP packets waiting to be serviced. Additional packets will be dropped. When setting this value, you're trading memory resources versus SNMP retries (only when the box is busy and gets behind on servicing the SNMP packets). Zero indicates there is no limit.

snmpProfile_CsmModemDiag.name: snmpProfile_CsmModemDiag
snmpProfile_CsmModemDiag.description: When set to `no' (its default value), SNMP CSM modem card diag is disabled. A JEDEC card is required to turn on this feature.

snmpProfile_SnmpMessageType.name: snmpProfile_SnmpMessageType
snmpProfile_SnmpMessageType.description: Indicate the message type that the SNMP agent should handle.

snmpProfile_SecurityLevel.name: snmpProfile_SecurityLevel
snmpProfile_SecurityLevel.description: Indicate the security level of the SNMP agent. Applicable only if SNMPv3 message handling enabled

snmpProfile_EnableVacm.name: snmpProfile_EnableVacm
snmpProfile_EnableVacm.description: If set to TRUE, View Based Access Control Model (VACM) would be enabled, otherwise VACM is disabled.

snmpProfile_NotificationLogAgeOut.name: snmpProfile_NotificationLogAgeOut
snmpProfile_NotificationLogAgeOut.description: The number of minutes a Notification SHOULD be kept in a log before it is automatically removed. A value of 0 means no age out.

snmpProfile_BitStringsAllowed.name: snmpProfile_BitStringsAllowed
snmpProfile_BitStringsAllowed.description: If enabled, TAOS agent responds to BITS data type in bit string format. If disabled, TAOS agent responds in numeric format.

snmpProfile_AlarmClearTableLimit.name: snmpProfile_AlarmClearTableLimit
snmpProfile_AlarmClearTableLimit.description: The maximum number of alarmCleared entries that can be held in the alarmCleared table.

mibsnmpv3NotifyProfileTable.name: mibsnmpv3NotifyProfileTable
mibsnmpv3NotifyProfileTable.description: A list of mibsnmpv3NotifyProfile profile entries.

mibsnmpv3NotifyProfileEntry.name: mibsnmpv3NotifyProfileEntry
mibsnmpv3NotifyProfileEntry.description: A mibsnmpv3NotifyProfile entry containing objects that maps to the parameters of mibsnmpv3NotifyProfile profile.

snmpv3NotifyProfile_Name.name: snmpv3NotifyProfile_Name
snmpv3NotifyProfile_Name.description: Any arbitrary, but unique identifier associated with this profile

snmpv3NotifyProfile_ActiveEnabled.name: snmpv3NotifyProfile_ActiveEnabled
snmpv3NotifyProfile_ActiveEnabled.description: TRUE if this profile is enabled for generation of SNMP messages

snmpv3NotifyProfile_Tag.name: snmpv3NotifyProfile_Tag
snmpv3NotifyProfile_Tag.description: Single tag value that is used to select entries in the snmpTargetAddrTable ( 'trap' profile). If this contains a string of zero length, no entries are selected.

snmpv3NotifyProfile_Type.name: snmpv3NotifyProfile_Type
snmpv3NotifyProfile_Type.description: Type of notification to be generated, i.e., Trap (unconfirmed class) or Inform (confirmed class). This field is for future use. Agent does not generate INFORM pdus.

mibsnmpv3TargetParamProfileTable.name: mibsnmpv3TargetParamProfileTable
mibsnmpv3TargetParamProfileTable.description: A list of mibsnmpv3TargetParamProfile profile entries.

mibsnmpv3TargetParamProfileEntry.name: mibsnmpv3TargetParamProfileEntry
mibsnmpv3TargetParamProfileEntry.description: A mibsnmpv3TargetParamProfile entry containing objects that maps to the parameters of mibsnmpv3TargetParamProfile profile.

snmpv3TargetParamProfile_Name.name: snmpv3TargetParamProfile_Name
snmpv3TargetParamProfile_Name.description: Any arbitrary, but unique identifier associated with this profile

snmpv3TargetParamProfile_ActiveEnabled.name: snmpv3TargetParamProfile_ActiveEnabled
snmpv3TargetParamProfile_ActiveEnabled.description: TRUE if this profile is enabled for generation of SNMP messages

snmpv3TargetParamProfile_MsgProcModel.name: snmpv3TargetParamProfile_MsgProcModel
snmpv3TargetParamProfile_MsgProcModel.description: Message processing model used when generating SNMP messages using this entry

snmpv3TargetParamProfile_SecurityModel.name: snmpv3TargetParamProfile_SecurityModel
snmpv3TargetParamProfile_SecurityModel.description: Security model to be used when generating SNMP messages using this entry

snmpv3TargetParamProfile_SecurityName.name: snmpv3TargetParamProfile_SecurityName
snmpv3TargetParamProfile_SecurityName.description: Security name which identifies the principal on whose behalf SNMP messages will be generated using this entry. This name should be a valid snmpv3-usm-user

snmpv3TargetParamProfile_SecurityLevel.name: snmpv3TargetParamProfile_SecurityLevel
snmpv3TargetParamProfile_SecurityLevel.description: Level of security to be used when generating messages using this entry.
